Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the pasta. Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Thinly slice the @tomato{1%medium}(thinly sliced).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once the oil is hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g} and stir-fry until golden, ~{4-5%minutes}.
> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook lardons thoroughly.

Add the garlic and @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g} and stir-fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Meanwhile, when your pan of water is boiling, add the @linguine{180%g} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back into the saucepan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Stir the @chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1%300g tin}, @chicken stock paste{10%g}, @Worcester sauce{15%ml}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{100%ml} into the bacon pan. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to low. Simmer until thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

Once the pasta is cooked, add to your sauce with half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}. Toss to coat, then season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add a splash of @water{} if it's a little thick. Warm through until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pop the @wild rocket{40%g} into a #medium bowl{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

When ready, share the bacon linguine between your bowls and sprinkle with the remaining cheese. Serve the rocket in bowls alongside topped with the sliced tomato and a drizzle of the @balsamic glaze{12%ml}. Enjoy!